casebody.data:
Roberts, Respondent, v. Pike, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. March 6, 1891.) Appeal from special term.

Argued before Daly, C. J., and Allen and Pryor, JJ.

Wm. North, for appellant. M. P. Stafford, for respondent.

No opinion. Judgment affirmed, with costs. See 13 N. Y. Supp. 559.
